  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nWhy should this feature exist?\r\nGeth has a useful --datadir.ancient parameter to allow splitting of this folder to cheaper, slower storage such as HDD and use SDD for the main indexes.\r\n\r\nWhat are the use-cases?\r\nThis can be done now by using symbolic links, but it is fickle and prone to error.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\nI am not sure if the snapshot/db folder would be best on slow storage or on SSD. Perhaps first port of call would be the move this out of snapshot folder to e.g. snapshot_db and thus just have the .idx, .torrent and .seg files inside snapshot.\r\n",
